    "Eventually, a self-learning clinical LLM might deliver a broad range of psychotherapeutic interventions while measuring patient outcomes and adapting its approach on the fly in response to changes in the patient (or lack thereof).",
    "Current approaches to psychotherapy often are unable to provide guidance on the best approach to treatment when an individual has a complex presentation, which is often the rule rather than being the exception.",
    "For example, providers are likely to have greatly differing treatment plans for a patient with concurrent PTSD, substance use, chronic pain, and significant interpersonal difficulties.",
    "Models that use a data-driven approach (rather than a provider's educated guess) to address an individual's presenting concern alongside their comorbidities, sociodemographic factors, history, and responses to the current treatment, may ultimately offer the best chance at maximizing patient benefit.",
    "While there have been some advances in precision medicine approaches in behavioral healthcare 54, 58, these efforts are in their infancy and limited by sample sizes 59."
